<Base title="Pathfinding — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <nav><a href="/pathfinding/">← Pathfinding</a></nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 7, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>If you plan as a guest, Pathfinding stores your trips only on your device. If you sign in, your
     account and trips are stored on our server so they sync across your devices.</p>

  <h2>Guest mode</h2>
  <p>In guest mode, your itineraries and preferences stay on your device. We receive no personal data.</p>

  <h2>Accounts</h2>
  <p>If you sign in, we store your email address (or your Apple ID identifier) and an authentication
     token. When you use email sign-in, your password is hashed before storage; we never see it in
     plain text.</p>

  <h2>Your trips</h2>
  <p>Itineraries you create — destinations, dates, notes, and the messages you send the AI planner —
     are stored on our server under your account so they sync and can be shared. They're used only to
     generate and store your plans.</p>

  <h2>AI planning</h2>
  <p>To build itineraries, your planning messages are sent to a language-model provider. We send only
     the text needed to produce your plan, and require our provider not to retain it for training.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <p>No ads. No selling your data. No third-party trackers. We don't use your trips for anything
     beyond running the service for you.</p>

  <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
  <p>Delete individual trips any time, or delete your whole account in Profile → settings. Removal is
     permanent.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy changes, the update will be posted here with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/pathfinding/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
